==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''male'': bad + ''fides'': faith.
===Adverb===
#(Law) Bad faith. 
#*MARITIME MOTORS (PTY) LTD v VON STEIGER AND ANOTHER 2001 (2) SA 584 (SE) @ 600
::Having regard to this [[dictum]] it is clear to me that the  plaintiff cannot rely on negotiorum gestorum to recover damages. The [[gestor]], ie the plaintiff, did not intend to serve the [[dominus]], ie the [[defendant]]s. The gestor did not act [[bona fide]] in the mistaken belief that he was serving the dominus. It was the plaintiff's evidence that in an attempt to preserve its good name and reputation it was decided to accept the cancellation of the agreement. It is thus clear that the gestor, the plaintiff acted '''mala fide''' in its own interest. In my view, the [[plaintiff]] cannot succeed on this principle of negotiorum gestorum.
